Class Grid

  • java.lang.Object
    • Grid

  • public class Grid
extends java.lang.Object
    A representation of a 2D grid, which can be used in many applications and have attached PathEdge operations applied to it.

      • Grid

        public Grid(java.lang.String fileName,
    int xBlocks,
    int yBlocks)
        Constructs a grid from a file given in fileName and the dimensions given. This uses the default cost values: A block of value 0 has a cost of 1 to traverse. A block of value 1 cannot be traversed. A block of value 2 has a cost of 3 to traverse. A block of value 3 has a cost of 10 to traverse.
        Parameters:
        fileName - The file name of the map file.
        xBlocks - The x dimension of the grid.
        yBlocks - The y dimension of the grid.
